        <updateDate>2021-04-14T19:58:03Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Slave-Free Business Certification Act of 2020</b><br> <br> This bill requires businesses with annual revenue greater than $500 million to audit their supply chains for labor practices or human trafficking activities that violate specified national or international standards and report the results to the Department of Labor.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
